This section describes how to install Pivotal GemFire.

-   **[OSX—Install Pivotal GemFire from a Homebrew Package](../../getting_started/installation/install_brew.html)**

    If your operating system is Mac OSX, you can install Pivotal GemFire from a Homebrew package.

-   **[RHEL—Install Pivotal GemFire from RPM](../../getting_started/installation/install_standalone_RHEL_nosuite.html)**

    If your guest operating system is Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL), you have the option to use the RPM distribution to install Pivotal GemFire. Complete the installation procedure on every virtual and physical machine that will run GemFire.

-   **[Ubuntu—Install Pivotal GemFire from a Debian Package](../../getting_started/installation/install_debian.html)**

    If your operating system is Ubuntu, you can install Pivotal GemFire from a Debian package.

-   **[Windows/Unix/Linux—Install Pivotal GemFire from a ZIP or tar.gz File](../../getting_started/installation/install_standalone.html)**

    For Windows, Solaris and all other Linux users, use the ZIP distribution to install and configure Pivotal GemFire on every physical and virtual machine where you will run Pivotal GemFire. You can also use .tar.gz file on Linux distributions.

-   **[Obtaining Pivotal GemFire from a Maven Repository](../../getting_started/installation/obtain_gemfire_maven.html)**

    You can use Maven to add Pivotal GemFire to your Java project build.

-   **[Obtaining Modified Open Source Code Libraries](../../getting_started/installation/obtaining_oss_files.html)**

    Many open source licenses require that vendors who use or modify their libraries make that code available. GemFire provides these libraries as a downloadable .zip file.

-   **[CLASSPATH Settings for GemFire Processes](../../../geode/getting_started/setup_gemfire_classpath.html)**

    This topic describes how GemFire processes set their CLASSPATH.

-   **[How to Uninstall GemFire](../../getting_started/installation/uninstall_gemfire.html)**

    This section describes how to remove GemFire.

# Obtaining and Installing Security Updates

New versions of Pivotal GemFire often include important security fixes, so Pivotal recommends you keep up to date with the latest releases.

For details about any security fixes in a particular release, see the [Pivotal security page](http://www.pivotal.io/security).
